cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper is primarily focused on distributed computing frameworks such as MapReduce and proposes a novel approach to reduce communication load among nodes. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper utilizes coding techniques to reduce communication load and improve computation-communication trade-off. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with communication load reduction in heterogeneous networks, which is a key aspect of networking and internet architecture. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a system-level approach to optimize computation-communication trade-off in distributed computing frameworks. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a novel combinatorial design to operate on heterogeneous networks, which involves designing efficient algorithms and data structures.
